# MemorAId UX/UI Rules

All UI work must follow `docs/UX_UI_MASTER.md`. The full spec is in `docs/UX_UI_*.md`.

## Hard Rules (blocking)

- No `max-width` that leaves >30% empty on wide screens
- No internal card/section padding < 12px
- No button height < 36px
- No `font-size` < 11px (except metadata)
- No contrast < 4.5:1 for regular text / < 3:1 for large text
- No `gap` < 4px between elements (except inline)
- No `border-radius` > 16px (except `rounded-full`)
- No arbitrary px/rem/color values – use Tokens from `client/src/index.css`
- No `:focus { outline: none }` without `:focus-visible` alternative
- No `<img>` without `alt`
- No icon-only button without `aria-label`
- No placeholder as sole label – always use `<label>`
- No error message that says only "שגיאה" – must include what+why+action
- Sidebar must visually mark the active page

## Before every PR touching UI

Run through `docs/UX_UI_ACCESSIBILITY_CHECKLIST.md` sections A–I.

## Tokens

Colors: `hsl(var(--token))` only. See `docs/UX_UI_TOKENS.md`.
Spacing: Tailwind scale only (space-1..24). See Spec §13.
Radius: `rounded-md` (8px), `rounded-xl` (12px), `rounded-full` only.

## Components

Use existing classes from `client/src/styles/design-system.css`:
- `.section-compact` / `.section-card` for all cards/sections
- `.data-row` for label|value rows
- `.badge`, `.badge-primary`, `.badge-success`, `.badge-destructive` for badges
- `.btn-primary` / `.btn-outline` for user app buttons

## Content

Button labels: verb first ("שמור", "הוסף מטופל", "פתח מדריך" – not "שלח בקשה" unless workflow exists).
Loading states: "שומר...", "שולח...", "מוחק...".
Errors: [מה קרה] + [למה] + [מה לעשות].

## RTL

Use `inline-start/end` logical properties. Flip directional icons with `rtl:-scale-x-100`.
